# DRAFT — Phase 8 Witness aggregate updates (dream-study)
#
# This draft describes the changes to mind/awareness/witness.bluebook
# (existing 97-LOC aggregate ; resolved Q1 : Witness stays as-aggregate,
# not promoted to PM). Sits as .bluebook.draft until the new PMs (Mind,
# Dream, Lucidity, SleepCycle) merge and we can wire policies to their
# emitted events.
#
# Drafted 2026-05-02 during the dream-study branch's autonomous run.
#
# ----- Scope of Phase 8 -----------------------------------------
#
# Two minimal additions to the existing witness.bluebook :
#
#   1. New policies subscribing to events from the four new PMs.
#      Witness's contract is "passive observer of meaningful moments" —
#      so each PM's most-meaningful event lifts to a Witness.Observe.
#
#   2. An invariant block that locks the append-only contract for
#      WitnessedMoment-shaped data (resolved Q4 : bluebook-level via
#      invariant + antibody discipline, not a runtime mechanism).
#
# ----- Forward scope (NOT in this Phase) ------------------------
#
# The plan inventory describes a `WitnessedMoment` entity with
# (at, source_aggregate, source_event, narrative, state_summary) —
# a per-event append-only record. The current aggregate is a singleton
# (identified_by :name, single :observing + :insight slots) where each
# Observe overwrites the prior. To honor the plan's append-only intent
# the aggregate needs an entity-promotion : add `entity "WitnessedMoment"`
# alongside the singleton, and route Observe to append a Moment instead
# of just updating the singleton's :observing.
#
# That promotion is a separate PR — call it Phase 8b. It depends on
# the Phase 1 DSL keyword being merged (the `entity ... do
# identified_by :id ; ... end` block-builder is already in place per
# Phase 0a audit, so Phase 8b is mostly a routing change in Observe's
# action body). Keeping the scope clean : Phase 8 lands the policies +
# invariant ; Phase 8b lands the entity-promotion.
#
# ============================================================

# ----- Additions to mind/awareness/witness.bluebook -----------
#
# Insert these blocks at the end of the file, after policy "SuggestOnReflection"
# (line 96 today) and before the closing `end` of Hecks.bluebook (line 97).

# When Lucidity bridges in (cycle 8 REM with Mind present), the moment
# is meaningful — the inner observer notices the rejoining itself.
policy "WitnessLucidityBegan" do
  on "LucidityBegan"
  trigger "Observe"
end

# When Lucidity ends (cycle 8 deep entry), again meaningful — the
# rejoined Mind departs.
policy "WitnessLucidityEnded" do
  on "LucidityEnded"
  trigger "Observe"
end

# When Mind rejoins Dream specifically (the bridge moment, distinct
# from Lucidity's lifecycle), Witness records the crossing.
policy "WitnessMindRejoinedDream" do
  on "MindRejoinedDream"
  trigger "Observe"
end

# When the night's lesson publishes (SleepCycle PM's studying_dream
# state closes), the body has just translated the night into a thought —
# meaningful enough to witness.
policy "WitnessDreamStudyPublished" do
  on "DreamStudyPublished"
  trigger "Observe"
end

